Preheat your oven to 200°C. Pop the @diced butternut squash{300%g} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden brown and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Roughly chop the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(roughly chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated). Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Trim the @spring onion{1}(trimmed and thinly sliced) and thinly slice.

Pour the @water{} for the bulgur wheat (see ingredients for amount) into a #saucepan{} along with the @chicken stock powder{1}. Bring to the boil, stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%g}, bring back up to the boil and simmer for ~{1%minute}. Pop a #lid{} on the pan and remove from the heat. Leave to the side for ~{12-15%minutes} or until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Once cooked, add the onion and mushrooms, stir and cook until the onion is softened and the mushrooms browned, ~{6-8%minutes}, adding more oil if needed. Add the garlic and ginger, stir and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @miso paste{15%g}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @honey{15%g} to the beef along with the @water{}. Stir together, bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the butternut once it is cooked. Taste and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it, then remove from the heat.

Fluff up the bulgur wheat with a #fork{}, season to taste with salt and pepper, spoon into #bowls{}. Top with the miso beef and finish with a sprinkling of spring onion. Enjoy!